# GitLevel — server-side environment variables.
# Set these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# A read-only token is enough: GitHub → Settings → Developer settings →
# Personal access tokens → Fine-grained token with NO extra permissions
# (public read access only). A classic PAT with no scopes also works.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Optional: extra tokens for rotation — a random token is picked per request
# to spread rate limits across them.
# PAT_1=
# PAT_2=

# Optional: a free Upstash Redis database (upstash.com — no credit card).
# Enables three things at once: a durable profile cache that survives cold
# starts, per-IP rate limiting on /api/card, and usage stats at /api/stats.
# Skip both and the deployment behaves exactly as it did before — in-memory
# cache only, no rate limiting, /api/stats reports enabled:false.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
